Fiona Joy
MIckey Quinns Live Music Hall and Irish Pub
13071 Park Blvd N., Seminole, FL, United States
Gifted singer-songwriter and multi-instrumentalist Fiona Joy (who we modestly note played her very first paid show at Quinns) has been called "to put it simply, excellent. She has a voice and an ability to perform like few I have seen, especially for her age.“ —Ken Apperson, Host of WMNF Live Music Showcase.
Fiona’s songs resonate with people of all ages, reflecting her keen insight and emotional depth. As a featured artist at the 2024 Florida Americana Music Festival, Fiona showcased her remarkable talent to a broader audience. But she never sounds better than she does LIVE in Quinns music hall!

MIckey Quinns Live Music Hall and Irish Pub
13071 Park Blvd N., Seminole, FL, United States
James Galione is a Lyricist/Songwriter/Composer from West Paterson, New Jersey, who found his home in Clearwater, Florida. His original compositions are Blues, Classic Rock, Country, Folk, Tribal, and Classical. His vocals have a sound somewhere between Joe Cocker, Tom Waits and Jim Morrison, but we've heard him light the room on fire anywhere from John Mellencamp to Jon Bon Jovi with the crowd on its feet for all of it. James is an artist you don't want to miss.

Gage Mooney
MIckey Quinns Live Music Hall and Irish Pub
13071 Park Blvd N., Seminole, FL, United States
Gage was raised in the mountains, and is a musician who finds his inspiration in the music he heard his grandfather play.
He's influenced by many genres of music that still play a role in his performances, but nothing has, can, or will pull the red dirt country road from between his toes.
You'll hear it in every note he plays and sings - he's on this earth to play songs that evoke emotion, and have a deeper meaning to himself and everyone around him.

Our Story
Mickey Quinn's opened in Seminole in 2003, and three generations have been coming here since to eat and drink, spend time with friends, listen to live local music, and enjoy fantastic and authentic Irish food.
We're named after Mickey Quinn, the Irish rugby player, whose sister Margaret first opened the pub in 2003, and whose recipes are the core of our original menu.
Quinn's is known for amazing food, a talented and fun bartenders, and live music every Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday, with open mic nights every Tuesday, 'living room' jam nights, trivia Mondays, late night karaoke on Thursdays (ladies night on Thursday too with killer drink pricing for the lassies.)
Indoors we have a music hall with a stage, 17 huge TV's, steel tip darts no charge to play, shuffleboard, foosball, all at no charge to play. If you're willing to part with 50 cents, we have arcade and other bar games, and a jukebox. On high volume nights like New Years Eve, Paddy's Day, and Quinnsgiving, we have an outdoor patio open for bands and large screen viewing.
We're open every day until 3am, to welcome all the service industry pros when they get off work from the beaches. The kitchen is open with hot food available all night long.
Come to Quinn's & hang out with all your friends. Raise your hands, move your feet, lift your voice.

LEGEND OF THE WHITE HAND:
``Why is there a plaster white hand on the wall by the door as you're leaving Quinn's?``
In Irish folklore, the white hand is a symbol used to keep the banshees away from your door. In the early 1900's the Irish ``white hand`` gang ran Al Capone out of New York and off to Chicago. At Quinn's, it does keep evil from the door. It doesn't stop Spectrum TV from continuing to try to bill us for two accounts... but REAL evil, it stops. Regulars sometimes high-five it. That may bring good luck - give it a try.
